Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum flirted with a triple-double, racking up 33 points, nine assists, and eight boards to lift the Boston Celtics to a 118-115 win over the Minnesota Timberwolves.
Derrick White scored 26 points for Boston, while Sam Hauser hit five three-pointers and scored 15 points.
Julius Randle led Minnesota with 27 points, eight rebounds and seven assists.
Naz Reid added 20 points off the bench, while Jaden McDaniels had 19 points and eight boards.
The Timberwolves trailed by eight with two minutes to play but had a chance to send it into overtime. However, Anthony Edwards’ three-pointer fell short at the buzzer.
